Package ohos.agp.animation.util

Interface TypeEstimator<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArgbEstimator, FloatArrayEstimator, FloatEstimator, IntArrayEstimator, IntEstimator, RectEstimator

    public interface TypeEstimator<T>
    Interface for use with the AnimatorValue.setEstimator(TypeEstimator) function.

    This class allows developers to create animations on arbitrary property types, by allowing them to supply custom estimators for types that are not automatically understood and used by the animation system.

    Since:
    7

      • estimate

        T estimate​(float progress,
           T startKeyValue,
           T endKeyValue)
        This function returns the result of linearly interpolating the start and end values, with progress representing the proportion between the start and end values.
        Parameters:
        progress - The progress from the starting to the ending values
        startKeyValue - The start value.
        endKeyValue - The end value.
        Returns:
        A linear interpolation between the start and end values, given the progress parameter.
